We recommended and Management agreed to the following:
a. The Municipal Treasurer immediately remit the amount of ₱1,108.70 to the office of the PAG-IBIG; and
b. The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer trace back transactions to identify the Municipal Officials and Employees that the prior year withholdings amounting to ₱3,957.08 for Due to GSIS and ₱8,543.56 for Due to Pag-ibig were due, and remit the said premiums/ loans or consider reconciling their records with the office of the GSIS and PAG-IBIG;

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to require the:
Municipal Accountant to continue to up-dating their PPE ledger cards for each PPE owned by the Municipality.
GSO to maintain property cards for all PPE owned by the Municipality;
Municipal Accountant and the GSO to reconcile the records of the Accounting Office and Property Officer on PPE;
Inventory Committee to (i) conduct physical count of PPE to determine the existence and condition thereof; and (ii) follow the new COA Circular 2020-006 re: Guidelines and Procedures in the Conduct of Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (PPE), Recognition of PPE Items Found at Station, and Disposition for Non-existing/Missing PPE Items, for the One-Time Cleansing of PPE Account Balances of Government Agencies;
Municipal Accountant to submit the depreciation schedule of the PPE items recognized in the Financial Statements, and
concerned Municipal officials to exert effort in the reproduction of titles on all lots owned by the Municipality to recognize these in the books of using the appraised values.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive and heads of concerned implementing offices agreed to:
(a) 	explain the failure to comply with the local budget circular;
(b) 	implement without further delay the remaining projects not completed/implemented in CY 2023; and
(c) 	continue to monitor and supervise the effective and efficient implementation of projects funded from various source agencies within the timelines in the MOA;
(d) 	update the uploaded data on the website and make the necessary posting as part of the public disclosure requirements; and
(e) 	continue to be prompt in the return of excess funds to the source agencies upon completion or termination of the project.

