We recommended that, in order to establish accurately and reliably the balances of local road networks and the related existence and condition thereof, the management undertake the following:
 The Municipal Engineer and the Municipal Property Custodian conduct a yearly physical count of local road network projects and consequently update the local road map of the LGU;
 The Municipal Engineer provide the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Property Custodian the description and cost segregation of road components of various road infrastructure projects;
 The Municipal Accountant to keep and maintain subsidiary leger for roads and its components and reconcile the same result of the physical inventory at the end of each year. Also, provide for the depreciation for the local road network and disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements; and
 The Municipal Property Custodian maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Cards for all roads and its components.

We have recommended the following:
 The Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer should trace back transactions to identify the municipal officials and employees the prior year withholdings were due, to remit the said premiums or consider reconciling their records with the office of the PAG-IBIG;
 Henceforth, remit promptly all contributions and payment of loans as mandated by R.A. No. 9679.

We recommend that the Municipal Government:
 Submit GPB to the PPDO of the Provincial Government to ensure the alignment of the municipal GAD PPAs with the priorities of the province. Then from PPDO to the DILG Regional Offices for review and approval;
 Identify GAD PPAs through the use of HGDG which would be the basis in the budget determination depending on its gender responsiveness or attribute to GAD interventions;
 Accompany GAD ARs with the reports/documents required to be furnished to COA to facilitate audit of GAD Fund utilization. Ensure that GAD ARs match with the GPB to facilitate the audit of GAD fund utilization; and
 Establish and/or strengthen the monitoring and evaluation systems to assess the effectiveness and efficiency of the gender mainstreaming efforts, and the M&E activities shall be included in the annual GPB

We recommend that the Municipal Government:
Submit GPB to the PPDO of the Provincial Government to ensure the alignment of the municipal GAD PPAs with the priorities of the province.  Then from PPDO to the DILG Regional Offices for review and approval;
Identify GAD PPAs through the use of HGDG which would be the basis in the budget determination depending on its gender responsiveness or attribute to GAD interventions;
Accompany GAD ARs with the reports/documents required to be furnished to COA to facilitate audit of GAD Fund utilization.  Ensure that GAD ARs match with the GPB to facilitate the audit of GAD fund utilization; and
Establish and/or strengthen the monitoring and evaluation systems to assess the effectiveness and efficiency of the gender mainstreaming efforts, and the M&E activities shall be included in the annual GPB.

In view of the foregoing observations, we have recommended that:

The Accountant obligate all cash advances granted and see to it that all cash advances are fully liquidated at year-end or as soon as the purpose of which it was granted has been served.  She should also see to it that cash advances for a particular year are not used to pay expenses of other years;
Management exert effort in collecting the said loans granted to NGOs/POs, LGU and individuals by sending demand letters.

We have recommended that the BAC and/or TWG:

Ensure that all bidding documents, including documentations on the conduct of detailed engineering are prepared/presented during the conduct of pre-procurement conference, and finalized prior to advertisement and/or posting of the Invitation to Bid;
Invite observers in all stages of the procurement process;
Advertise invitation to bid, and post Notice of Award and Notice to Proceed at the PhilGEPS website, at the entity’s website, if any, and in conspicuous places as required by R.A. 9184.  Henceforth, adhere to the transparency provision as this is one of the governing principles on government procurement;
Conduct thorough review and evaluation of the prospective bidder’s eligibilities and ensure that the prospective bidders submit complete and valid eligibility requirements before they are marked as “passed” and declared as LCRB;
Initial every page of the original copies of all bids received and opened during the bid opening to ensure integrity of submitted documents;
Submit copy of the complete contract documents to the Office of the Auditor within five (5) working days from perfection of the contract as required under  COA Circular No. 2009-001 for auditorial and technical review;
Strictly comply with the provisions of R.A. No. 9184 in the conduct of public bidding and awarding of contracts/ projects.  BAC members, BAC secretariat and the TWG should familiarize themselves with different rules and regulations set forth by R.A. No. 9184;
Submit written justification/s for non-adherence to provisions of R.A. No. 9184.

We have recommended that
Management:
 Require the conduct of detailed engineering as a basic requirement in all procurement of infrastructure projects;
 Adhere to the transparency provision as this is one of the governing principles on government procurement;
 BAC should invite observers in all stages of the procurement process;
 Ensure that prospective bidders submit complete eligibility requirements before they are marked as “passed” and declared as LCB;
 the BAC or their duly authorized representative, initial every page of the original copies of all bids received and opened during the bid opening to ensure integrity of submitted documents.
 Require the prospective bidders post the required performance security prior to contract signing and issuance of the Notice to Proceed;
 Copy of the contract documents be submitted to the Office of the Auditor within five (5) working days from perfection of the contract as required under COA Circular No. 2009-001 for auditorial and technical review;
 the Bids and Awards Committee should strictly comply with the provisions of R.A. No. 9184 in the conduct of public bidding and awarding of contracts/ projects. BAC members, BAC secretariat and the TWG should familiarize themselves with different rules and regulations set forth by R.A. No. 9184;
 BAC should submit written justification/s for non-adherence to provisions of R.A. No. 9184.
